Defendant Steven R Draeger in court with attorney Katie Elizabeth Babe.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Court addresses the WCS report showing SCRAM violation.    The Defendant enters a plea of guilty to Count #1.  The Court finds the Defendant guilty.  Counts #2 dismissed and read in.  Count #3 dismissed by operation of law.     
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following to begin forthwith, defendant taken into custody.

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 
5 YEARS 9 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 3 days)
  -  2 YEAR(S) 9 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full timeemployment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Victim Impact Panel;
*Do not drive without valid license;

FINE $3801.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

BLOOD DRAW FEE: $35.00 to City of Muskego Police Department (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

TRANSCRIPT FEE: $8.00 to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DL REVOCATION: 36 MONTHS;
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 MONTHS;

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program. (AFTER SERVING 18 MONTHS INITIAL CONFINEMENT);

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
